910
00:39:38,970 --> 00:39:40,680
And so why is this happening?

911
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:43,410
So if you allow me, I know
I'm running a little bit long,

912
00:39:43,410 --> 00:39:45,330
but I'll try to go through this fast,

913
00:39:45,330 --> 00:39:47,730
because it's kind of, I
think this is exciting,

914
00:39:47,730 --> 00:39:49,980
but to understand what's going on,

915
00:39:49,980 --> 00:39:53,460
you have to kind of go back
to your tight binding model,

916
00:39:53,460 --> 00:39:55,860
which is synonymous with 1D-SSH

917
00:39:55,860 --> 00:39:58,140
and parameterize the system

918
00:39:58,140 --> 00:40:01,740
to understand why we have
these closing HOMO-LUMO gaps

919
00:40:01,740 --> 00:40:04,770
and why we have this
increasing conductance.

920
00:40:04,770 --> 00:40:08,910
So polyacetylene has
been worked out years ago

921
00:40:08,910 --> 00:40:12,270
and, you know, one way
to kind of understand

922
00:40:12,270 --> 00:40:13,980
the different topological structures

923
00:40:13,980 --> 00:40:16,560
is to realize that the
double bond is just really

924
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:18,000
a hopping parameter.

925
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:19,110
Where there's a double bond,

926
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:21,030
the hopping probability is higher.

927
00:40:21,030 --> 00:40:23,880
And so if you describe
the hopping probability

928
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:26,010
in terms of delta like this,

929
00:40:26,010 --> 00:40:27,780
then all you have to
know is that when delta

930
00:40:27,780 --> 00:40:29,010
is greater than one,

931
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:30,860
you have this kind of structure where this

932
00:40:30,860 --> 00:40:32,430
is higher hopping probability,

933
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:34,050
so you have a double bond there.

934
00:40:34,050 --> 00:40:36,120
And when delta is less than one,

935
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:40,170
then you have this other topological state

936
00:40:40,170 --> 00:40:42,780
where now you've moved
your double bond over.

937
00:40:42,780 --> 00:40:45,390
And so by parameterizing
like this, you can now

938
00:40:45,390 --> 00:40:47,640
just write your simple
tight-binding Hamiltonian,

939
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:49,050
for those of you who are interested,

940
00:40:49,050 --> 00:40:51,630
and now you can solve it
as a function of delta,

941
00:40:51,630 --> 00:40:54,030
because t1 and t2 depend on delta.

942
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:56,880
So when you solve it for
different values of delta,

943
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:57,780
you get the following.

944
00:40:57,780 --> 00:41:01,650
You get your boring wide band gap molecule

945
00:41:01,650 --> 00:41:03,300
when delta is equal to one.

946
00:41:03,300 --> 00:41:06,270
You get narrowing HOMO-LUMO
gap when delta decreases.

947
00:41:06,270 --> 00:41:10,260
And finally in the topological
state, you get no gap.

948
00:41:10,260 --> 00:41:13,950
You get a gapless semiconductor, okay?

949
00:41:13,950 --> 00:41:17,550
So this is just extrapolated
for all values of delta.

950
00:41:17,550 --> 00:41:20,490
And now we can take this spectrum,

951
00:41:20,490 --> 00:41:22,290
these are just eigenstate solutions

952
00:41:22,290 --> 00:41:24,150
to this tight-binding Hamiltonian

953
00:41:24,150 --> 00:41:26,580
and we can use non-equilibrium
Green's function

954
00:41:26,580 --> 00:41:27,810
to calculate transmission.

955
00:41:27,810 --> 00:41:28,643
So all you have to do is,

956
00:41:28,643 --> 00:41:30,450
I'm just gonna take these resonances

957
00:41:30,450 --> 00:41:33,480
and now I'm going to
predict transmission, okay?

958
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:35,520
So for this

959
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:37,180
boring wide band gap

960
00:41:38,340 --> 00:41:40,410
molecule, you get wide bang gap,

961
00:41:40,410 --> 00:41:44,253
and so you have low conductance
at the fermi energy.

962
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:47,310
For the intermediate case,

963
00:41:47,310 --> 00:41:49,890
you have a narrower HOMO-LUMO gap

964
00:41:49,890 --> 00:41:51,690
and so you have higher conductance,

965
00:41:51,690 --> 00:41:56,310
and for this topological
system, you get no gap.

966
00:41:56,310 --> 00:42:00,390
But of course it's impossible
to stabilize the system,

967
00:42:00,390 --> 00:42:04,050
and so I'm going to look at
this delta equal to 0 case,

968
00:42:04,050 --> 00:42:05,340
the intermediate case,

969
00:42:05,340 --> 00:42:08,460
because there's actually
a physical analog to this,

970
00:42:08,460 --> 00:42:11,670
and we can see whether this model agrees

971
00:42:11,670 --> 00:42:13,290
with experimental results.

972
00:42:13,290 --> 00:42:16,380
So the physical model I'm
going to use is cumulene.

973
00:42:16,380 --> 00:42:18,690
I know it's not the same exactly,

974
00:42:18,690 --> 00:42:21,570
but it's a system where you
have perfect delocalization,

975
00:42:21,570 --> 00:42:24,660
because you have these
double bonds at every site.

976
00:42:24,660 --> 00:42:29,010
And so, you know, I think this
is a reasonable approximation

977
00:42:29,010 --> 00:42:30,420
to the cumulene case.

978
00:42:30,420 --> 00:42:33,600
And the cumulene case has
been measured experimentally.

979
00:42:33,600 --> 00:42:36,300
And I already mentioned to
you that what they measured

980
00:42:36,300 --> 00:42:39,900
is a very kind of gradual
slight increase in conductance.

981
00:42:39,900 --> 00:42:41,610
So if you look here, it's, you know,

982
00:42:41,610 --> 00:42:43,530
it's all within one order of magnitude.

983
00:42:43,530 --> 00:42:45,660
It's within actually half
an order of magnitude.

984
00:42:45,660 --> 00:42:47,340
So it's basically flat.

985
00:42:47,340 --> 00:42:48,900
You make the molecules longer

986
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:50,790
and the conductance stays flat.

987
00:42:50,790 --> 00:42:52,080
And if you look here,

988
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:54,720
that's exactly what our model predicts.

989
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:58,620
So this 1D-SSH predicts that
you make the molecules longer,

990
00:42:58,620 --> 00:43:00,750
but the conductance here at fermi,

991
00:43:00,750 --> 00:43:04,020
which is where we measure
it, stays the same.

992
00:43:04,020 --> 00:43:05,580
So how can this be?

993
00:43:05,580 --> 00:43:09,240
So the only way that you can
have a closing HOMO-LUMO gap,

994
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:12,570
but a conductance that doesn't
increase is if you have some

995
00:43:12,570 --> 00:43:15,810
sort of destructive quantum
interference canceling the fact

996
00:43:15,810 --> 00:43:17,640
that the gap is closing.

997
00:43:17,640 --> 00:43:19,230
So this is really a signature

998
00:43:19,230 --> 00:43:21,570
that there's destructive
quantum interference effects

999
00:43:21,570 --> 00:43:25,383
at play here that keep
your conductance low.

1000
00:43:27,750 --> 00:43:29,640
And this is just showing that if you look

1001
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:30,900
at delta equal to 0,

1002
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:33,510
the CQI terms, the
constructive interference

1003
00:43:33,510 --> 00:43:35,730
really cancel out the
destructive interference,

1004
00:43:35,730 --> 00:43:39,360
and so you just get flat
conductance, no enhancement.

1005
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:42,780
Okay, what about these molecules?

1006
00:43:42,780 --> 00:43:43,980
And now we'll just, you know,

1007
00:43:43,980 --> 00:43:45,900
reveal the result that there

1008
00:43:45,900 --> 00:43:48,180
is no such destructive
quantum interference

1009
00:43:48,180 --> 00:43:49,410
in these molecules and

1010
00:43:49,410 --> 00:43:53,040
that's why you have this
dramatic increase in conductance.

1011
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:56,130
So just briefly, how do we see this?

